# Observability

rio-build provides three pillars of observability: logs, metrics, and traces.

## Build Log Storage

### Log Lifecycle

<div class="tracey-req" id="r-obs.log.batch-64-100ms"><a class="tracey-req-anchor" href="#r-obs.log.batch-64-100ms">obs.log.batch-64-100ms</a><span class="tracey-req-badges"><span class="tracey-badge impl">impl 2<div class="tracey-popover"><a href="https://github.com/x/y/blob/main/src/scheduler.rs#L42">src/scheduler.rs:42</a><a href="https://github.com/x/y/blob/main/src/worker.rs#L128">src/worker.rs:128</a></div></span><span class="tracey-badge verify">verify 1<div class="tracey-popover"><a href="https://github.com/x/y/blob/main/tests/log_test.rs#L15">tests/log_test.rs:15</a></div></span></span></div>

Log lines are batched (up to 64 lines or 100ms, whichever first) in `BuildLogBatch` messages.

<div class="tracey-req" id="r-obs.log.periodic-flush"><a class="tracey-req-anchor" href="#r-obs.log.periodic-flush">obs.log.periodic-flush</a><span class="tracey-req-badges"><span class="tracey-badge impl">impl 1<div class="tracey-popover"><a href="https://github.com/x/y/blob/main/src/scheduler.rs#L89">src/scheduler.rs:89</a></div></span><span class="tracey-badge verify zero">verify 0</span></span></div>

The scheduler flushes buffers to S3 periodically (every 30s) during active builds.

## Metrics

### Gateway Metrics

<div class="tracey-req" id="r-obs.metric.gateway"><a class="tracey-req-anchor" href="#r-obs.metric.gateway">obs.metric.gateway</a><span class="tracey-req-badges"><span class="tracey-badge impl zero">impl 0</span><span class="tracey-badge verify zero">verify 0</span></span></div>

| Metric | Type | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| `rio_gateway_connections_total` | Counter | Total SSH connections |
| `rio_gateway_connections_active` | Gauge | Currently active connections |
